   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">During the relay test the relay switches to its active state.
Before starting make sure that it is approved to perform the test,
especially if the active relay signal triggers a remote action.</prereq>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">If a relay is tested that opens a
system breaker, like the EPO signal, the load will no longer be supplied.</note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step id="M_User-Access_Service" class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure you are logged in
as a user with <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Service</uicontrol> access. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note "> If you are not logged in, a prompt to login will appear
when trying to change mode.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main menu icon</uicontrol> and navigate
to <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Service &gt; General &gt; Relaytest &gt; Relaytest</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If necessary, expand the section for the input/output card
to show the programmed relays.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">For more information about the relays refer to the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Drawings</i>.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Press on the <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Start</uicontrol> button for the relay you want to test.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig platform="Modular-DC Modular-Inverter Modular-AC Prime-UPS"
                    class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Relaytest_0000755265.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <fig platform="Modular-DCDC-Converter" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Relaytest_Reality-Logo_DD00674975.png"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <result class="- topic/section task/result ">For a few seconds the relay will change to its active state
for a short time (open if normally closed, closed if normally open).
Check that the connected signal was correctly activated when the relay
state changes.</result>
